did.unittitle: Paul E. Sluby, Sr. Cemetery Research Collection

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: Files are arranged alphabetically by cemetery name, followed by cemetery-related topics. Processed without series.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Paul E. Sluby, Sr. was born in Canonsburg, Pennsylvania on November 23, 1934. Mr. Sluby retired from the District of Columbia Metropolitan Police. He was a certified genealogist as well as a legal researcher and historian. Mr. Sluby died on March 27, 2019.

custodhist.head: Custodial History
custodhist.p: Paul E. Sluby, Sr. donated his cemetery research files to the Library in 2012.

custodhist.head: Custodial History
custodhist.p: Paul E. Sluby, Sr. donated his cemetery research files to the Library in 2012.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: General processing procedures included refoldering of items into archival, acid-free folders. Folder labels and physical arrangement of the materials were not changed; Sluby's original organization was retained.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection consists of newspaper clippings, E-mails, and Sluby's notes on various cemeteries in Washington, D.C. Files are arranged alphabetically by cemetery name, followed by cemetery-related topics.
